  </p>

  <h2>
    Checkboxes & Radio Buttons
  </h2>
  <p>
    Whenever there are multiple options, you should wrap them in a
    <code>fieldset</code> with a <code>legend</code> that describes the set of
    options.
  </p>
  <p>
    If the user should be allowed to choose multiple options, use checkboxes. If
    they can only choose one of the options, use radio buttons. These styles are
    written for explicitly labeled inputs, so be sure to use <code>for</code>
    and <code>id</code> attributes instead of wrapping inputs with labels.
  </p>
  <p>
    Always use <code>name</code> and <code>value</code> attributes so the users'
    choices are correctly selected.
  </p>

